CASCADE OUTAGE — REAL ROOT CAUSE FOUND+FIXED (2026-06-02 ~07:25). After E0428 fix (4c4ed3f) + cache fixes (27eeea8) + error-surfacing (7c843db/a0363de) the actual blocker surfaced in the CI ::error:: annotation: rust-lld: error: rs_learn-*.rcgu.o: undefined symbol: host_kv_put / host_kv_get. It was NEVER a second source compile error - it is a wasm LINK error in the rs-learn dependency crate. rs-learn/crates/wasm/src/wasm_host.rs declared host_kv_get/put/query/host_vec_search/host_log/host_now_ms in a BARE extern C block (no #[link(wasm_import_module=env)]). When rs-learn is linked as a dep rlib into the rs-plugkit wasm cdylib under --release with LINUX rust-lld, the dep-crate env imports were not merged with the cdylib imports -> undefined symbols. WINDOWS rust-lld tolerated it (my exact-CI-cmd local release build EXIT=0 both with committed and fresh Cargo.lock), which is EXACTLY why no local reproduction (cargo check, cargo build --release, fresh-lock, wasi-sdk-24) ever caught it - it is a Linux-rust-lld-only cross-crate import-merge error. FIX (rs-learn 47f2804): added #[link(wasm_import_module=\"env\")] above the extern block; env matches plugkit-wasm-wrapper.js importObject.env. KEY LESSONS: (1) a wasm host-import extern block in ANY crate that becomes a dep of a wasm cdylib MUST carry #[link(wasm_import_module=...)] or Linux rust-lld release-links it as undefined - bare extern C only survives because the final cdylibs imports resolve and lenient linkers (Windows) tolerate the dep mismatch. (2) cargo check and even cargo build --release on a DIFFERENT host OS can both pass while CI fails - the linker differs by host; CI ::error:: annotation surfacing (echo ::error:: from the failed build step) was the decisive diagnostic since CI job logs are admin-403. (3) the 5-day outage was a STACK of three independent issues each masking the next: E0428 dup (compile) -> [cache/observability] -> rs-learn link error - layered-hidden-bugs, crackable only by fix-deploy-observe-next. VALIDATION PENDING: rs-learn 47f2804 cascade -> rs-plugkit release pulls fixed rs-learn -> Build-WASM link succeeds -> publish-binaries ships plugkit-bin > v0.1.616 -> gm.json bumps.